    "attributes": {
        "action": "Appoint an independent panel to conduct a Public Inquiry into the DSA / DVSA",
        "additional_details": "The scope should include but not limited to historic unresolved complaints since 1992: \r\nHow complaints are handled\r\nHow requests of access to data/records are handled\r\nHow many Driving Instructors PDI/ADIs have been wrongly removed from the DVSA register and lost their job\r\nIf all DVSA examiners are properly trained to conduct driving tests for pupils with disabilities \r\nWho is responsible for direct/indirect/discrimination\r\nThe independent panel to determine the truth & accountability",
        "background": "Call the Government to appoint an independent panel to carry out a full public inquiry into the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency and whether it is fit to continue to administer driving tests & the ADI register. Also to look at concerns of misuse of its powers & obstructing candidate complaints.",
